-- Poland's PZU buys stake in local rival Link4 from Britain's RSA
-- 
-- Thu Apr 17, 2014 02:37AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, April 17 (Reuters) - Central and eastern Europe's largest insurer PZU <PZU.WA> bought a stake in its Polish rival Link4 from Britain's RSA <RSA.L> for 90 million euros ($124.26 million), pending adjustments, PZU said in a statement on Thursday.

